ancouver, reportsthe Mirror.\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1387, \"end\": 1396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 4.84659675830527e-12, \"text\": \"Vancouver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will draw from the third book in Rick Riordan's series, titled The Titan's Curse.\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1454, \"end\": 1466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rick_Riordan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rick Riordan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rick_Riordan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rick_Riordan\"}, {\"begin\": 1488, \"end\": 1493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Titans\", \"score\": 0.9999999999940883, \"rank\": 5.858990774153598e-12, \"text\": \"Titan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Titans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Titans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the novel's official synopsis: \\\"When Percy Jackson gets an urgent distress call from his friend Grover, he immediately prepares for battle.\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1553, \"end\": 1566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Percy_Jackson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.556640660962348e-79, \"text\": \"Percy Jackson\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Percy_Jackson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Percy_Jackson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He knows he will need his powerful demigod allies at his side, his trusty bronze sword Riptide, and... a ride from his mom.\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1779, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The demigods rush to the rescue to find that Grover has made